    "name": "Hemolysis prediction performance requirement for CPB CFD model",
    "description": "The CFD model shall demonstrate acceptable predictive performance for hemolysis-relevant quantities of interest across the intended operating envelope. Specifically, the model shall exhibit minimal systematic bias in shear stress predictions and shall reproduce hemolysis trends with reasonable fidelity relative to available experimental reference data. Model outputs shall not deviate substantially from measured values under representative operating conditions, and the overall simulation quality shall be consistent with established best practices for cardiovascular CFD applications.",
    "acceptanceCriteria": "Model predictions are considered acceptable when systematic bias remains at a minimal level and hemolysis index agreement is within a reasonable range of experimental reference values. Compliance is assessed by the credibility team in accordance with applicable cardiovascular CFD guidelines."
